'''Anthony Hewitt''' (born in 1971) is a classical pianist from the [[Lake District]], [[England]]. <ref>{{cite news|author = DONALD ROSENBERG|title = PLAYING GROWS LIVELIER AS CONTEST PROGRESSES|quote = |publisher = Plain Dealer |date = August 10, 1997|url = |accessdate = January 23, 2011}}</ref><ref name="argus"/>
Described by ''The Gramophone'' as 'a remarkably gifted artist',<ref name="argus">{{cite news|author = |title = Hewitt comes to shine light on sunny Cape; English pianist plans annual late-summer working holidays in city|quote = |publisher = Cape Argus|date = February 23, 2008|url = |accessdate = January 23, 2011}}</ref> and by [[Alfred Brendel]] as 'a young pianist of remarkable talent', Hewitt now combines his busy concert schedule with the duties of directing the Ulverston International Music Festival.<ref>{{cite news|author = Adrian Mullen|title = Another top notch line-up for Ulverston International Music Festival|quote = |publisher = The Westmorland Gazette|date = May 25, 2009|url = |accessdate = January 23, 2011}}</ref>
